<task id="integrating-webhelp-plugin-with-dita-ot">
    <title>Installing and Integrating the <ph keyref="product"></ph> with the DITA Open
    Toolkit</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Integration with DITA OT</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>The requirements of the <ph keyref="product"></ph> for the DITA Open Toolkit are as
          follows:<ul id="ul_jcr_211_gs">
          <li>Java Virtual Machine 1.8 or newer if you want to use DITA-OT <ph
              keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT2xVer"></ph> or Java Virtual Machine 1.6 or newer if you
            want to use DITA-OT <ph keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT18Ver"></ph>.</li>
          <li>DITA Open Toolkit <ph keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT2xVer"></ph> (includes Saxon 9.x
            libraries) or DITA Open Toolkit <ph keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT18Ver"></ph>.<note>The
                <ph keyref="product"></ph> has only been tested with these two specific versions
                (<b>DITA-OT <ph keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT2xVer"></ph></b> and <b>DITA-OT <ph
                  keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT18Ver"></ph></b>). It is possible that the plugin may
              work with other versions, but only the two tested versions are fully
            supported.</note></li>
        </ul></p>
      <p>To install and  integrate the <ph keyref="product"></ph> with the DITA Open Toolkit, follow
        these steps:</p>
    </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
        <cmd><ph id="JVM">Download and install a <xref
              href="http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html"
              format="html" scope="external">Java Virtual Machine</xref> version compatible with the
            DITA-OT version.</ph></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Download and unpack the <xref href="http://www.dita-ot.org/download" format="html"
            scope="external">DITA Open Toolkit</xref> version <ph keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT2xVer"
          ></ph> or <ph keyref="webhelpPluginDITAOT18Ver"></ph>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-webhelp-chapter/step_donwload"></ph></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-webhelp-chapter/step_copy_content"></ph></cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><xref href="register-webhelp-plugin.dita#register-webhelp-plugin">Register your license
            key</xref>:</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Open the <filepath><abbreviated-form keyref="glossentry_dita_ot_dir"
                />/plugins/com.oxygenxml.webhelp.classic</filepath> directory, create a file called
                <filepath>licensekey.txt</filepath>, and copy your license key that you purchased
              for your <ph keyref="product"></ph>.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Do the same thing for the <term>Responsive</term> variant. Open the
                  <filepath><abbreviated-form keyref="glossentry_dita_ot_dir"
                />/plugins/com.oxygenxml.webhelp.responsive</filepath> directory, create a file
              called <filepath>licensekey.txt</filepath>, and copy your license key that you
              purchased for your <ph keyref="product"></ph>.</cmd>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph conkeyref="reusables-webhelp-chapter/step_run_integrator"></ph></cmd>
      </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
